The minimum denomination for this security is [%$PARM1%] ("Minimum").  There are purchases and sales of this security in the secondary market below the Minimum ("Odd Lots").  There can be no assurance that there will be a market for Odd Lots in the future.  If there is a market for Odd Lots, it may be less liquid than the market for the Minimum or for an amount in excess of the Minimum.  Investors desiring to sell this security should be aware that it may be more difficult to obtain a bid for an Odd Lot than for the Minimum or for an amount in excess of the Minimum.  Any bid for an Odd Lot may be less than a bid price for the Minimum or for an amount in excess of the Minimum.  Investors who own Odd Lots may be limited in their ability to participate in corporate actions, including but not limited to partial calls and tender and exchange offers.  This security is "book entry" and will be held in your brokerage account.  In exceptional circumstances the issuer may choose to issue certificates for this security.  However, the issuer will not issue certificates for Odd Lots.  (SBS-EXEC-0123)

Cryptocurrency-related products carry a substantial level of risk and are not suitable for all investors. Investments in cryptocurrencies are relatively new, highly speculative, and may be subject to extreme price volatility, illiquidity, and increased risk of loss, including your entire investment in the fund. Spot markets on which cryptocurrencies trade are relatively new and largely unregulated, and therefore, may be more exposed to fraud and security breaches than established, regulated exchanges for other financial assets or instruments. Some cryptocurrency-related products use futures contracts to attempt to duplicate the performance of an investment in cryptocurrency, which may result in unpredictable pricing, higher transaction costs, and performance that fails to track the price of the reference cryptocurrency as intended.
